description: Numbers whose cubes contain more than half the same digit and do not end in 0.
example: 173^3=5177717, whose digits are more than half 7's.
mathematica: nchdQ[n_]:=Module[{dc=DigitCount[n^3],idn=IntegerDigits[n^3]},Max[ dc]>Length[ idn]/2 && Last[idn]>0]; Select[Range[21000],nchdQ] (* _Harvey P. Dale_, Jul 13 2012 *)
author: _Erich Friedman_, Apr 29 2001
